snippet.title: [TripstarGram] DRIPPIN at Yeosu - #bemykorea #tripstargram #Yeosu #Drippin
snippet.description:
"Tripstagram," where we travel in Korea with K-Pop stars! The first travel destination with DRIPPIN is Yeosu, Jeollanam-do. They enjoy the fantastic scenery of Hyangiram Hermitage and earn travel expenses through games. And a thrilling attraction mission awaits them! snippet.title: [DanstarGram] Ep 2. E’LAST at Gangneung

Gangneung city is loved for its crystal clear waters of the East Sea and the vast nature.
Global popular group and 4th generation performance masters!
K-pop group E’LAST is in Gangneung!

They did a surprise busking performance at Wolhwa Street and the main busking event was done at the Central Square in Gyeongpo Beach.

Global rising star EPEX has come to TripStarGram! Their destination is Mokpo, Jeollanam-do Province. EPEX rides a cable car across to Gohado Island. What does the great hero Admiral Yi Sun-sin, whom they meet on a beautiful coastal promenade, look like? Mokpo, where you can enjoy desserts on the streets with the modern culture of the 19th century and the faraway past in a time when dinosaurs were alive. snippet.title: [Full Episode] Against All Odds: Insooni’s Miracle Busking | 📍 Hongcheon, Gangwon-do
snippet.description:
🎶𝗠𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗰 𝗟𝗶𝘀𝘁🎶
0:38 Against All Odds - Christian Burgos & Lara Benito (Original Song by Phil Collins)
4:49 My Reflection in My Heart - Christian Burgos (Original Song by Yoo Jae-ha)
13:41 Fly Me to the Moon - Insooni & Haeun Jang (Original Song by Bart Howard)  
17:56 Don't Know Why - Lara Benito & Haeun Jang (Original Song by Norah Jones)
21:45 If (Korean&Spanish Ver.) - Lara Benito (Original Song by Taeyeon)
27:37 Uphill Road - Hyelin of EXID (Original Song by Jung-in, Yoon Jong-shin)
35:10 Goose's Dream - Insooni

📌𝗣𝗲𝗿𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗩𝗲𝗻𝘂𝗲: Mugunghwa Arboretum▶https://goo.gl/maps/Hq3r8YZGHTFAimgf9

📝Insooni’s Miracle Busking ‘Against All Odds’ has two goals: 
First, introduce the hidden travel destinations to further prevent overtourism. 
Second, send out the message that we should let our children live in the world accepting each other’s differences. 

✨𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗿𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴: 
- Insooni 
- Christian Burgos 
- Lara Benito 
- Hyelin of EXID
- Haeun Jang
- Ko Hyun-sook 

🎶공연곡 목록🎶
0:38 Against All Odds - 크리스티안 부르고스 & 라라 베니또 (원곡: 필 콜린스)
4:49 내 마음에 비친 내 모습 - 크리스티안 부르고스 (원곡: 유재하)
13:41 Fly Me to the Moon - 인순이(노래) & 장하은(연주) (원곡: 바트 하워드)  
17:56 Don't Know Why - 라라 베니또(노래) & 장하은(연주) (원곡: 노라 존스)
21:45 만약에 (한국어&스페인어 Ver.) - 라라 베니또 (원곡: 태연)
27:37 오르막길 - 혜린(EXID) (원곡: 정인, 윤종신)
35:10 거위의 꿈 - 인순이 

📌공연 장소: 무궁화수목원▶https://goo.gl/maps/Hq3r8YZGHTFAimgf9

📝숨겨진 여행지 소개를 통해 오버투어리즘(Overtourism)을 방지하고, "다름을 인정하며 함께 사는 세상을 아이들에게 남기자"는 메시지를 세상에 전하려는 인순이와 AAO 팀의 단단한 발걸음! 기적의 버스킹, '어게인스트 올 오즈'! 

✨출연: 
- 인순이
- 크리스티안 부르고스
- 라라 베니또
- 혜린(EXID)
- 장하은 
- 고현숙 

#AgainstAllOdds #AAO #Insooni 
#어게인스트올오즈 #인순이

📝The Travel Track members' last trip together! Their final destination for the grand finale is Geojedo Island! Here, the members enjoy the thrill of the jetboat and admire the beauty of nature, such as the Haegeumgang Islets. Their meal today is made from the fish they caught themselves, and for dessert, they try Bamboo Leaf Makgeolli with Seafood and Green Onion Pancakes. While eating, they talk about the past moments they shared.

📝트래블 트랙 멤버들의 마지막 여행! 그 대미를 장식하는 여행 장소는 바로 거제! 언제나 스릴과 자연을 사랑해 온 멤버들답게 거제의 아름다운 바다 위에서 제트보트를 타며 해금강을 즐긴다. 직접 낚시한 물고기로 배불리 식사도 하고, 맹종죽 테마파크를 한적하게 거닐다 지난 여행들에 대한 소회를 밝히기도 한다. 수다에 막걸리와 죽순전을 곁들이는 건 덤.

📝The Travel Track members arrived at Jeju, at last! At Jeju, time flies in the blink of an eye. One should take a pic of the day with windmills and then ride a jetboat or a transparent kayak. After that, stomachs should be filled up with cuttlefish, which are in season during summer. Last but not least, everyone should not miss the chance to listen to the sounds of nature at Jeju Gotjawal Provincial Park. My, what a busy day!

📝드디어 제주도에 입도한 트래블 트랙 멤버들! 제주도에서는 언제나 하루가 짧다. 우선 풍차를 배경으로 인생샷을 찍은 다음, 제트보트와 투명 카약을 타고, 격렬한 물놀이 끝에 출출해진 배를 제철 한치로 채운다. 게다가 제주곶자왈도립공원에서 제주도의 푸른 자연이 들려주는 소리까지 느끼려니, 바쁘다, 바빠!

📝A day in Incheon for the Travel Track members begins with a glamorous yacht tour. 📝Last week, the Travel Track members climbed Daedunsan Mountain with all their might. This week, the members' stamina is once again tested at Mungyeong. On a hot summer day, members head to the top of Gomosanseong Fortress to admire the scenery. For those who overcame the hardship, Dansan Monorail is prepared as compensation! After that, only fun stuff, such as paragliding and enjoying the theme park 'Ecorala,' remain!

snippet.description:

📝The Travel Track members, who are experts in eating, playing, and resting, came to Boryeong! How can they miss the Boryeong Mud Festival while they are so passionate about having fun? After being soaked with mud from head to toe, everyone is craving food. And don't tell me you are gonna leave Boryeong without tasting the grilled shellfish since there is an all-you-can-eat restaurant by the ocean! With their full tummies, the members lastly arrive at Sanghwawon for the perfect finale of their trip to Boryeong. Wandering around in nature while feeling the traditional atmosphere of Korea... What a day! 

✏️0:54 2022보령해양머드박람회 📌https://goo.gl/maps/8JnwiFeHLNKwksNJ7

📝잘 놀고, 잘 먹고, 잘 쉬는 4인방이 보령에 등장했다! 재미있는 경험이라면 사족을 못 쓰는 트래블 트랙 멤버들이 보령머드축제를 그냥 지나칠 수 있을 리가! 온몸이 진흙투성이가 되고 나니 슬슬 밥 생각이 난다. 바닷가에서는 역시 조개구이를 먹어 줘야 하는 것 아닐까? 심지어 조개구이가 무한리필이니 말이다! 조갯살로 꽉 찬 배를 두드리며 도착한 곳은 바로 상화원이다. 자연 속에서 한국만의 정취를 느끼며 산책을 하고 있자니, 완벽하다, 보령 여행!

After successfully completing Daedunsan Mountain's 3-Level Thrill Course(the cable car, the Suspension Bridge, Samseon Stairway), the members choose to eat the whole chicken soup and the chicken stew with ripe kimchi by Daea Reservoir to boost their energy. This is not the end, because the healthy healing experience fully begins at Andeok Village!

snippet.title: Travel in Wanju | Why Exhaust Yourself When You Can Ride the Cable Car? | Travel Track
snippet.description:
Is it possible to complete a 600m route in 6 minutes? If you ride on the Daedunsan Cable Car, it is not impossible at all! Oh, and don't forget to watch the picturesque scenery through the cable car's whole glass walls! 

📌Daedunsan Cable Car: https://goo.gl/maps/7FWT58uvf7QULMKAA

snippet.description:

snippet.title: 📍Travel in Incheon | Pentaport Rock Festival Rocks the City🎸 | 🎬Travel Track
snippet.description:
It is impossible not to participate in the rock festival while you are at Incheon. And you know what? You can also drink beer while you enjoy the music! A rock festival with a glass of cold beer - can you think of anything more heavenly than that? 

📌Incheon Pentaport Rock Festival (Songdo Moonlight Festival Park): https://goo.gl/maps/ybKKhCvR19qqUGAUA 

✅Go check the full Travel Track episodes right now!

snippet.title: 📍Travel in Incheon | The Taste of White Jajangmyeon🍜 | 🎬Travel Track
snippet.description:
Why is Chinatown in Incheon so special? Because one can taste Chinese dishes made in an exclusive Korean style! For instance, have you ever heard of "white" jajangmyeon? Usually, jajangmyeon is made with black soybean sauce, but here at Incheon Chinatown, the sauce is white! 

📌Incheon Chinatown: https://goo.gl/maps/bzpGiCKJM4dVSHbb6

▶Full Travel Episode: https://youtu.be/oKoVXwNiRug

인천의 차이나타운이 특별한 이유는 무엇일까? 바로 한국만의 스타일로 재해석한 중국 요리들을 맛볼 수 있기 때문! 예를 들어, "하얀짜장"에 대해 들어본 적이 있는가? 대부분의 자장면은 검은색 춘장으로 만들지만, 여기 인천 차이나타운에는 하얀 자장면이 있다!

snippet.title: [Wonder Frame] Trip into Mongolia from Korea ✈️🐎 | 한국에서 몽골로 꿈틀 문화여행
snippet.description:
Mongolian Culture Trip with Mongolian and Korean friends 🏹

Wonder Frame to find Mongolia
Mongolian YouTuber zolboo living in Korea wants to show the true side of Mongolia to Korean friends.
Zolboo, Mongolian friend Od, and Korean friend Ga Young participateed in the Wonder frame Program held in Sangam-dong, Seoul and find out there are unknown place in Jeju island where related in Mongolia.
They visited Jeju Island in search of Mongolian culture that can be found in Korea,
and through Mongolians living there, They learned about Mongolia that they didn't know before.

몽골로 떠난 꿈틀문화여행
한국에 살고 있는 몽골인 유튜브 Zolboo는 몽골의 진정한 모습을 한국인 친구에게 보여주고 싶다.
서울 상암동에서 열린 꿈틀문화여행 프로그램에 참가한 졸부와 몽골인 친구 어드, 한국인 친구 가영은 한국에서 찾을 수 있는 몽골 문화를 찾아 제주도를 방문하고 그 곳에서 살고 있는 몽골인을 통해 그 동안 몰랐던 몽골에 대해 알게 된다.


0:00 Intro
0:35 Opening(Introducing Zolboo, Od and Ga Young)
1:58 Off to Mongolia by plane
3:11 Passport picture is done with caricature
4:17 Ger from Mongolia
6:12 Manners are needed for entering Ger
9:10 Get the quiz right, get a Mongolian souvenir
12:12 Experiencing mongolian culture in Jeju Island
13:01 Performance with horses in The Ma Park
22:35 United with Samgyeopsal
25:02 Closing


#Mongolian #Zolboo #Od #culturetrip #wonderframe #Ger #youtuber

snippet.title: [Wonder Frame]👩🏻‍❤️‍👩🏻Trip into Thailand from Korea with Energizer Prae🛬 | 에너자이저 프레와 함께 떠나는 태국 문화여행
snippet.description:
Wonder Frame to find Thailand
The Thai Prae, who became famous Youtuber in Korea while studying abroad in Korea has a dream of traveling with his Korean friend Joohyun to Thailand.
Prae and Joohyun, who participated in the Wonder frame program in Sangam-dong, Seoul,
learned that there was a Thai temple in Korea and They visit there.
There, Prae and Joohyun have a Buddhist service and took pictures with Thai people who visited there for the holiday and They get the energy and courage to living in Korea.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

태국으로 떠난 꿈틀문화여행
한국에 유학와 유튜버로 유명해진 프래는 한국인 친구 주현과 함께 태국 여행을 가는 꿈을 가지고 있다.
서울 상암동에서 열린 꿈틀문화여행에 참여한 프래와 주현은 한국에도 태국 절이 있다는 것을 알게되고 그곳을 방문하기로 한다.
그곳에서 프래와 주현은 휴일을 맞아 그곳을 방문한 태국인들과 함께 예불을 하고 사진을 찍으며 열심히 생활할 기운과 용기를 얻는다.

0:00 Intro
0:32 Opening(Introducing Prae and Joohyun)
1:33 Off to Thailand by plane
3:20 Passport picture made through caricature❄️
5:05 Traditional Thai game Aikla 🧿
6:56 Thai traditional clothes🥻
8:42 Finding the perfect Thailand trip destination based on MBTI
11:12 Thai temple in Korea(Wat Buddharangsee seoul temple)
15:10 Thai shop(Nam Phrik, Pad Thai noodles, Lottery, Thai chili, Papaya)
18:30 Thai restaurant(Thai Pho, Som Tam, Sticky rice)
21:56 Trying to find peace of mind by freeing the fish
24:35 Closing

#Papaya #Nam Phrik
